<subSubSection id="E0B66549FFBA2854FF1DF8CC2D07A20C" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="307" pageId="3" pageNumber="306" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="A81336C2FFBA2854FF1DF8CC2D07A20C" blockId="3.[151,1437,1807,2013]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1436,151,285]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="307" pageId="3" pageNumber="306">
<taxonomicName id="6FAC4D41FFBA2853FF1DF8CC2FB1A45C" box="[199,436,1844,1869]" class="Insecta" family="Bittacidae" genus="Bittacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brunipennis">
<emphasis id="9AD8EAD0FFBA2853FF1DF8CC2FB1A45C" box="[199,436,1844,1869]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="306">Bittacus brunipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is one of the three species of the “group 
<taxonomicName id="6FAC4D41FFBA2853FC72F8CC2A11A45D" authorityName=": Souza Lopes &amp; Mangabeira" authorityYear="1942" box="[936,1044,1845,1868]" class="Insecta" family="Bittacidae" genus="Bittacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angrensis">
<emphasis id="9AD8EAD0FFBA2853FC72F8CC2A11A45D" box="[936,1044,1845,1868]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="306">angrensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” (see comments in 
<taxonomicName id="6FAC4D41FFBA2853FAD9F8CC2B97A45D" authorityName=": Souza Lopes &amp; Mangabeira" authorityYear="1942" box="[1283,1426,1845,1868]" class="Insecta" family="Bittacidae" genus="Bittacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angrensis">
<emphasis id="9AD8EAD0FFBA2853FAD9F8CC2B97A45D" box="[1283,1426,1845,1868]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="306">B. angrensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="CC3D4B33FFBA2853FF44F8AE2FC3A461" author="Collucci, E. &amp; Amorim, D. S." box="[158,454,1879,1904]" pageId="3" pageNumber="306" pagination="1 - 8" refId="ref14802" refString="Collucci, E. &amp; Amorim, D. S. (2000) Three new species of Thyridates Navas, 1908 (Mecoptera, Bittacidae) from Brazil, with new combinations and some comments about phylogenetic relationships within the genus. Contribuicoes Avulsas Sobre a Historia Natural do Brasil, Serie Zoologia, 21, 1 - 8." type="journal article" year="2000">Collucci &amp; Amorim 2000</bibRefCitation>
). The species is known only by the female 
<typeStatus id="77178860FFBA2853FC72F8AE2A08A461" box="[936,1037,1879,1904]" pageId="3" pageNumber="306">holotype</typeStatus>
, which is very similar to specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="6FAC4D41FFBA2853FF61F8842F49A485" authorityName=": Souza Lopes &amp; Mangabeira" authorityYear="1942" box="[187,332,1917,1940]" class="Insecta" family="Bittacidae" genus="Bittacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angrensis">
<emphasis id="9AD8EAD0FFBA2853FF61F8842F49A485" box="[187,332,1917,1940]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="306">B. angrensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This similarity was noted by 
<bibRefCitation id="CC3D4B33FFBA2853FD1FF8852A08A485" author="Collucci, E. &amp; Amorim, D. S." box="[709,1037,1916,1941]" pageId="3" pageNumber="306" pagination="1 - 8" refId="ref14802" refString="Collucci, E. &amp; Amorim, D. S. (2000) Three new species of Thyridates Navas, 1908 (Mecoptera, Bittacidae) from Brazil, with new combinations and some comments about phylogenetic relationships within the genus. Contribuicoes Avulsas Sobre a Historia Natural do Brasil, Serie Zoologia, 21, 1 - 8." type="journal article" year="2000">Collucci &amp; Amorim (2000)</bibRefCitation>
, who mentioned the color of the pterostigma as the main character to distinguish these two species. This character however, does not seem very strong, since it shows some plasticity in other species of 
<taxonomicName id="6FAC4D41FFBA2853FC9AF83C2D99A4CD" box="[832,924,1989,2012]" class="Insecta" family="Bittacidae" genus="Bittacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9AD8EAD0FFBA2853FC9AF83C2D99A4CD" box="[832,924,1989,2012]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="306">Bittacus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, suggesting that 
<taxonomicName id="6FAC4D41FFBA2853FBBDF83C2B14A4CC" box="[1127,1297,1988,2013]" class="Insecta" family="Bittacidae" genus="Bittacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brunipennis">
<emphasis id="9AD8EAD0FFBA2853FBBDF83C2B14A4CC" box="[1127,1297,1988,2013]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="306">B. brunipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
might be a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="6FAC4D41FFBD2854FEFDFF602FB1A3A1" authorityName=": Souza Lopes &amp; Mangabeira" authorityYear="1942" box="[295,436,153,176]" class="Insecta" family="Bittacidae" genus="Bittacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angrensis">
<emphasis id="9AD8EAD0FFBD2854FEFDFF602FB1A3A1" box="[295,436,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="307">B. angrensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Because the species was described from a female, the identification of 
<taxonomicName id="6FAC4D41FFBD2854FB2FFF602B99A3A1" box="[1269,1436,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Bittacidae" genus="Bittacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brunipennis">
<emphasis id="9AD8EAD0FFBD2854FB2FFF602B99A3A1" box="[1269,1436,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="307">B. brunipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
remains uncertain mainly because the shape of the male epandrium is one of the most important characters to distinguish 
<taxonomicName id="6FAC4D41FFBD2854FEC0FF182F73A3E9" box="[282,374,225,248]" class="Insecta" family="Bittacidae" genus="Bittacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9AD8EAD0FFBD2854FEC0FF182F73A3E9" box="[282,374,225,248]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="307">Bittacus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species. The collection of male specimens close to the type locality, Campos do Jordão State Park (
<collectingRegion id="6A68F820FFBD2854FF03FEFD2F55A20C" box="[217,336,260,285]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="4" pageNumber="307">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
), will be needed to solve this question.
</paragraph>
